It is an unpardonable offence when one discovers that where one was
convinced of being loved, one is only regarded as a household utensil
and decoration, whereby the master of the house can find an outlet for
his vanity before his guests.
%
What else is love but understanding and rejoicing that another lives,
works, and feels in a different and opposite way to ourselves? That love
may be able to bridge over the contrasts by joys, we must not remove
or deny those contrasts. Even self-love presupposes an irreconcileable
duality (or plurality) in one person.
