I admit that my head is set wrong on my neck only, for every other man,
as is well known, knows better than I what I should do or leave alone. The
only one who cannot help me is myself, poor beggar! Are we not all like
statues on which false heads have been placed? Eh, dear neighbour?—Ah
no; you, just you, are the exception!
