A good friendship arises when the one man deeply respects the other,
more even than himself; loves him also, though not so much as himself;
and finally, to facilitate intercourse, knows how to add the delicate
bloom and veneer of intimacy, but at the same time wisely refrains from
a true, real intimacy, from the confounding of _meum_ and _tuum_.
