“_GAUDEAMUS IGITUR._”—Joy must contain edifying and healing forces
for the moral nature of man. Otherwise, how comes it that our soul, as
soon as it basks in the sunshine of joy, unconsciously vows to itself,
“I will be good!” “I will become perfect!” and is at once seized
by a premonition of perfection that is like a shudder of religious awe?
